[center][img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/logo.png?raw=true[/img]

[size=14px]This [b]forge[/b] modification adds new unique enchantments to the game.
I have tried to add enchantments that fit Minecraft and ensure that they were as
balanced as possible. A detailed description of all enchantments can be found on the [url=https://github.com/Majrusz/MajruszsEnchantmentsMod/wiki]Wiki[/url].[/size]
[style size=14px color=#f00]Since version 1.0.0 this mod requires a [url=/mod/majrusz-library/][color=#f00]Majrusz Library[/color][/url][/style][style size=14px color=#f00] to work![/style]

[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/changes.png?raw=true[/img]

[size=14px]- [b]17+[/b] new enchantments and [b]5+[/b] new curses
- all enchantments are highly configurable in the configuration file
- shields and horse armors are now enchantable
- supports [b]Enchantment Descriptions[/b]
- supports [b]JEI Enchantment Info[/b][/size]

[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/stuff.png?raw=true[/img]

[style b size=18px]Fuse Cutter[/style]
[size=14px]Cancels nearby explosions when the player blocks with a shield.[/size]
[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/fuse_cutter.gif?raw=true[/img]

[style b size=18px]Telekinesis[/style]
[size=14px]Adds items directly to the inventory if possible, when mining blocks and killing mobs.[/size]
[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/telekinesis.gif?raw=true[/img]

[style b size=18px]Sixth Sense[/style]
[size=14px]Eavesdrops on the footsteps of mobs and highlights them for a few seconds.[/size]
[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/sixth_sense.gif?raw=true[/img]

[style b size=18px]Frost Rider[/style]
[size=14px]Creates frosted ice blocks when a horse is walking over water.[/size]
[img]https://github.com/Majrusz/MinecraftCommon/blob/main/Enchantments/frost_rider.gif?raw=true[/img]

[style b size=18px]And much more![/style]

